At the same time, DOGE and Musk framed these cuts as heroic savings. The DOGE website removed detailed data that had previously allowed independent verification of budget claims, and Musk\'92s office overstated savings by tens of billions of dollars. Musk appeared on Fox Business to describe Social Security as a Ponzi scheme and called for workforce cuts, using his quasi\uc0\u8209 official platform to shape public perceptions of core social insurance programs. When the Musk Watch DOGE Tracker, launched by Popular Information, documented that most touted savings were unverifiable, Musk attacked the watchdog rather than addressing its findings.\
