This combination of centralized cost\uc0\u8209 cutting power and manipulated fiscal narratives shifted both substance and perception. Essential services\'97veterans\'92 care, school nutrition, local food purchasing, and in\u8209 person access to benefits\'97were reduced or made harder to reach, while the public was told that waste had been painlessly trimmed. The civil service became more precarious and politicized, as job security and union protections eroded, and the data needed to contest these changes thinned.\
