Environmental and climate policy formed a seventh front. The Environmental Protection Agency announced 31 rollbacks of regulations, including rules on electric vehicles and coal, shifting power toward fossil\uc0\u8209 fuel interests. The administration moved to reconsider the 2009 greenhouse gas endangerment finding, threatening the legal foundation for many climate rules. Support for renewable energy and climate resilience programs at home and abroad was rolled back, while a permit for a major liquefied natural gas export project off Louisiana was extended, locking in carbon\u8209 intensive infrastructure.\
