An eighth development concerned information, media, and memory. The administration defunded the U.S. Agency for Global Media, including Voice of America and other broadcasters, stripping resources from congressionally chartered outlets that had provided independent reporting abroad. At USAID, leadership ordered staff to shred or burn agency records despite preservation laws, a direct attempt to erase documentation of how foreign aid decisions were made. In parallel, the Education Department\'92s civil\uc0\u8209 rights layoffs and the cancellation of medical research grants narrowed the production and enforcement of knowledge about discrimination and public health.\
