The final development of the week played out in the realm of norms, religion, and electoral legitimacy, where erosion and resistance coexisted. Trump renewed false claims that the 2020 election had been rigged and called for jailing unnamed perpetrators, further undermining trust in electoral outcomes and framing political adversaries as criminals. Paula White, director of the White House Faith Office, urged legal challenges to the separation of church and state to reintroduce prayer and Bibles in public schools, signaling an official project to fuse religious authority with state power.\
